Naobi-no-Kami is believed to purify {{ill|Kegare|ja|穢れ}} (pollution or defilement) and rectify misfortune (禍, ''maga'').<ref>[http://www.norinaga.jp/shoin/naobitama.html Original Text on Naobi-no-Kami]</ref>
In the context of {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話}}, during the {{ill|Birth of the Gods|ja|神産み}}, when {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ}} returned from {{ill|Yomi|ja|黄泉}} and performed a {{ill|Misogi|ja|禊}} (ritual purification) to cleanse himself of the defilement from Yomi, the deity {{ill|Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|禍津日神}} was born from the impurity. To counteract the calamities brought about by Magatsuhi-no-Kami, Naobi-no-Kami was born. According to the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}}'', after the emergence of {{ill|Yaso-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|八十禍津日神}} and {{ill|Ō-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|大禍津日神}}, three deities were born: {{ill|Kami-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|神直毘神}} (神直毘神), {{ill|Ō-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|大直毘神}} (大直毘神), and {{ill|Izanome-no-Kami|ja|伊豆能売}}. In the ''{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}}'', in the fifth chapter, sixth alternate writing, after the creation of {{ill|Yaso-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|八十枉津日神}}, the two deities {{ill|Kami-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|神直日神}} and {{ill|Ō-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|大直日神}} are mentioned. In the tenth alternate writing of the same chapter, it is stated that Izanagi created Ō-Naobi-no-Kami during his purification, followed by the creation of {{ill|Ō-Ayatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|大綾津日神}} (considered identical to Ō-Magatsuhi-no-Kami).
