'''Naobi-no-Kami''' (直毘神, pronounced as ''Naobi no Kami'') is a [[:en:Shinto|Shinto]] deity.

Naobi-no-Kami is believed to purify [[:en:Kegare|Kegare]] (pollution or defilement) and rectify misfortune (禍, ''maga'').<ref>[http://www.norinaga.jp/shoin/naobitama.html Original Text on Naobi-no-Kami]</ref>

In the context of [[:en:Japanese mythology|Japanese mythology]], during the [[:en:Kamiumi|Birth of the Gods]], when [[:en:Izanagi|Izanagi]] returned from [[:en:Yomi|Yomi]] and performed a [[:en:Misogi|Misogi]] (ritual purification) to cleanse himself of the defilement from Yomi, the deity {{ill|Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|禍津日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Magatsuhi-no-Kami|qq=}} was born from the impurity. To counteract the calamities brought about by Magatsuhi-no-Kami, Naobi-no-Kami was born. According to the ''[[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]]'', after the emergence of {{ill|Yaso-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|八十禍津日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yaso-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 禍津日神}} and {{ill|Ō-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|大禍津日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ō-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 禍津日神}}, three deities were born: {{ill|Kami-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|神直毘神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami-Naobi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 神直日神}} (神直毘神), {{ill|Ō-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|大直毘神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ō-Naobi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 直毘神}} (大直毘神), and {{ill|Izanome-no-Kami|ja|伊豆能売|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanome-no-Kami|qq=}}. In the ''[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]'', in the fifth chapter, sixth alternate writing, after the creation of {{ill|Yaso-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|八十枉津日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yaso-Magatsuhi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 禍津日神}}, the two deities {{ill|Kami-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|神直日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami-Naobi-no-Kami|qq=}} and {{ill|Ō-Naobi-no-Kami|ja|大直日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ō-Naobi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 直毘神}} are mentioned. In the tenth alternate writing of the same chapter, it is stated that Izanagi created Ō-Naobi-no-Kami during his purification, followed by the creation of {{ill|Ō-Ayatsuhi-no-Kami|ja|大綾津日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ō-Ayatsuhi-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 禍津日神}} (considered identical to Ō-Magatsuhi-no-Kami).
